data.title: Kay Kay Menon to watch Chandrayaan 3's lunar landing with family: A historic moment
meta_keywords: kay kay menon talks about chandrayaan 3
data.meta_description: In an exclusive interview with IndiaToday. in, Kay Kay Menon has expressed his excitement and pride about the upcoming Chandrayaan 3's landing on the moon, hoping India will successfully achieve this historic feat.
data.text:
Chandrayaan's lunar landing is a proud moment for us all. As Indians, it is a matter of pride. The commencement of the countdown for Chandrayaan 3's lunar landing mission is underway, with the spacecraft anticipated to execute a gentle touchdown on the Moon's surface on August 23, 2023.

In anticipation of this significant event, Kay Kay Menon, in an exclusive chat with IndiaToday.in, conveyed his enthusiasm, considering it a moment of immense pride for all Indians. The critically acclaimed actor has even made plans to witness the remarkable lunar landing of Chandrayaan 3 alongside his family and friends.

advertisement

KAY KAY MENON ON CHANDRAYAAN

Actor Kay Kay Menon, in a recent chat with IndiaToday.in spoke about how incredible Chandrayaan is. He mentioned that it is a huge moment in the history of India. The 'Special Ops' actor said, "I plan to watch it with my family and friends. It's a huge historic moment and my heartiest congratulations to ISRO. I believe no one has landed on the moon and I believe nothing has happened till now."

He also said how he also hopes for India to successfully land the satellite. "I really hope that we are the first ones to land a satellite on the moon, so for us as Indians, it's a big moment. Even if we don't achieve it, it is an incredible moment for all of us. Kudos to ISRO and the entire team for this big achievement and we are just waiting for it to happen," Kay Kay Menon stated.

ON THE WORK FRONT FOR KAY KAY MENON

Kay Kay was last seen in the Raj and DK web series, 'Farzi', alongside Shahid Kapoor and Vijay Sethupathi. He will be next seen in 'Love All'. The sports drama is written, directed and produced by Sudhanshu Sharma. Swastika Mukherjee will also feature in this film.
